lyrics:
4 contributorsstation lyricsverse 1
was it in a dream i wouldnt know
i was in the lowlands where all the old folks go
i wasnt here i wasnt home
i was picking static up on a broken radio

chorus
just leave me at the station and you can rest assured
that ill be back sometime this time next year

verse 2
ill pack my bags you get the door
heres a stack of tokens for my friends on baltimore
that look on your face ive seen it before
ill be gone a long time but i could be gone for more

chorus

outro
i need someone
i need something
i need to go back homesee dr dog liveget tickets as low as 72you might also likeembed
